parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch module can cause the vehicle to stall unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic. Additionally, it can also cause electrical shorts, fires, and damage to the dashboard and steering column.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
often while driving at moderate speeds or when making turns
the ignition switch overheats
the steering column smokes
the dashboard electrical system catches on fire
and the vehicle experiences electrical shorts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the drive gear on the distributor shaft can cause the vehicle to stall, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
often without warning
and the drive gear on the distributor shaft is cut in the wrong direction to match the gear on the crankshaft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause electrical shorts, fires, and damage to the dashboard and steering column, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The dashboard electrical system catches on fire
the steering column smokes
and the vehicle experiences electrical shorts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and failure can cause loss of power brakes and power steering, increasing the risk of accidents, and in some cases, lead to vehicle fires.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls after warming up
the vehicle stalls when coming to a stop
the vehicle has difficulty starting or intermittently stalls
the air filter catches on fire
the vehicle catches on fire while running.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Idle Air Control Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the idle air control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
the gas pedal accelerates by itself
the engine RPM increases suddenly
the vehicle stalls or hesitates
especially in cold weather or snowy conditions.
